description: Aspose.Diagram is a class library for working with Microsoft Visio files. It allows developers to create new diagrams and work with VSD, VSDX, VSTX, VSSX, VSS, VST, VSX, VTX, VDW and VDX files on ASP.NET web applications, web services and Windows applications. It allows you to open files and manipulate the elements of the diagram, from lines and fills, to more complex elements, and then export to VDX, VSX,VSDX,VSSX,VSTX, VTX, XPS, HTML, SVG, SWF, XAML, image or PDF formats.
releaseNotes:
This release introduces the features, enhancements,task and bug fixes as detailed below:
    
    New Features
   DIAGRAMNET-50221-Add support to insert text labels
   
    Enhancements

   DIAGRAMNET-51095-Can't add shape menu item (action)
   
    Bugs

   DIAGRAMNET-50347-VSDX to PDF export, incorrect font of bold text items
   DIAGRAMNET-50713-VSD to PDF export - the bounding box color of the form icons is changed
   DIAGRAMNET-50870-Background color of the shape is changed on converting a VSD to PDF
   DIAGRAMNET-50872-Background Color of the shapes is changed on converting a VSD to PDF
   DIAGRAMNET-50877-The background color of shapes is changed on saving VSD to PDF

   DIAGRAMNET-51062-Missing shapes on converting a VST to PDF
   DIAGRAMNET-51089-The background color of the page is not being preserved on converting a VSD to SVG
   DIAGRAMNET-51090-Open and Save VSDX - the cross signs appear in place various shapes
   DIAGRAMNET-51091-Open and save VSDX - the text of the shape turns into dummy characters

summary: Aspose.Diagram is a class library for working with Microsoft Visio files.
title: Aspose.Diagram for .NET
